          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1708526051193-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>diced chicken breast</strong> and cook for a further 4-5 min or until beginning to brown</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708526056951-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708526056951-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708526056951-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708526056951-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708526056951-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and <strong>cornflour </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708526061072-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708526061072-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708526061072-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708526061072-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708526061072-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and<strong> </strong>your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>remaining toasted sesame oil </strong>with your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and mix it all together</p><p>Cook for 6-7 min or until the chicken has cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened to a gravy-like consistency – this is your <strong>golden crown chicken curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708526065565-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708526065565-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708526065565-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708526065565-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708526065565-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>golden crown chicken curry</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Top with the <strong>crunchy chilli oil </strong>and <strong>reserved sliced spring onion</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave the crunchy chilli oil and spring onion!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
